    {
        "sha": "73b26e5fcb0dd3f08fbf1a63318deedec5cc6cee",
        "author": "Aleksandr Kirsanov",
        "email": "unserialize.alias@gmail.com",
        "date": "2023-04-26T15:28:39Z",
        "message": "Support tmpfs and a server queue for C++ compilers (#10)\n\nThis PR drops an option -working-dir, adding two new instead:\r\n* -cpp-dir {string}, Directory for incoming C++ files and src cache\r\n* -obj-dir {string}, Directory for resulting obj files and obj cache\r\nThe directory passed as -cpp-dir can be placed in tmpfs.\r\n\r\nAlso, nocc-server now managers C++ compiler launches with a waiting queue. \r\nThe purpose of a waiting queue is not to over-utilize server resources at peak times.",
        "url": "https://github.com/VKCOM/nocc/commit/73b26e5fcb0dd3f08fbf1a63318deedec5cc6cee"
    },
    {
        "sha": "edc04d3cdd82c50568ae6433754a2d1293d3f580",
        "author": "Aleksandr Kirsanov",
        "email": "unserialize.alias@gmail.com",
        "date": "2023-03-22T14:44:14Z",
        "message": "correctly expand __FILE__ on a server-side by using relative paths (#6)\n\nBefore, a client send cppInFile as an abs file name, and a server launched\r\n> g++ /{clientWorkingDir}/{cppInFile}\r\nNow, a client sends cppInFile exactly the same as it was specified in cmd line,\r\nand besides, it sends cwd.\r\nOn a server, we launch g++ in a dir {clientWorkingDir}/{cwd} and pass\r\n> g++ {cppInFile}\r\ndirectly, as a relative one, which leads to __FILE__\r\nexpanded equally to client launch.",
        "url": "https://github.com/VKCOM/nocc/commit/edc04d3cdd82c50568ae6433754a2d1293d3f580"
    },
    {
        "sha": "ab52095b760785fe106c8935a16bfd0096b95e63",
        "author": "Aleksandr Kirsanov",
        "email": "unserialize.alias@gmail.com",
        "date": "2023-02-07T15:59:26Z",
        "message": "allow to compile non-uploaded files in /usr folder (#3)",
        "url": "https://github.com/VKCOM/nocc/commit/ab52095b760785fe106c8935a16bfd0096b95e63"
    },
    {
        "sha": "45562250a6ff21e5b0b9cf45eb2af361468bc7f4",
        "author": "Aleksandr Kirsanov",
        "email": "unserialize.alias@gmail.com",
        "date": "2023-01-30T11:43:23Z",
        "message": "support depfiles generation: -MF -MT -MQ -MD -MMD -MP (#1)\n\nThese flags are used in CMake/make projects to generate .o.d files \r\nalong with an object file (\"as a side effect of the compilation\")",
        "url": "https://github.com/VKCOM/nocc/commit/45562250a6ff21e5b0b9cf45eb2af361468bc7f4"
    },
